element.name: UCISA Commercial Engagement

element.name: UCISA Digital Communication Mgt
element.documentation: What the organisation does to facilitate communications between stakeholders over digital channels and ensure that new channels are identified and adopted as required.

element.name: UCISA Compliance Monitoring & Reporting

element.name: UCISA Research Administration
element.documentation: All activities aimed at administering and supporting the organisation's research environment.

element.name: UCISA Research Compliance Mgt
element.documentation: What the organisation does to manage and ensure compliance with research rules and regulations, including ethics.

element.name: UCISA Accommodation Incident & Emergency Response
element.documentation: What the organisation does to ensure it is able to react and respond appropriately to emergencies and other serious incidents that occur in or affect student accommodation, including the ability to keep residents safely housed even during occurrences that mean standard accommodation is temporarily vacated.

element.name: UCISA Manage Research Relationships
element.documentation: What the organisation does to plan, manage and cultivate its research relationships with other organisations, including the management of partner relationships and for knowledge exchange relationships.

element.name: UCISA Research Funding
element.documentation: All activities aimed at obtaining and managing funds to undertake research projects.

element.name: UCISA Government Relationship Mgt
element.documentation: What the organisation does to ensure it effectively manages and maintains its ties with government bodies.

element.name: UCISA Dispute Resolution
element.documentation: What the organisation does to manage and resolve legal and legislative disputes.

element.name: UCISA ICT Service Support
element.documentation: What the organisation does to ensure the delivery of customer focused ICT service support.

element.name: UCISA Training & Development
element.documentation: What the organisation does to ensure the acquisition of new, or enhancement of existing, knowledge and skills by its employees in order to provide the desired level of performance.

element.name: UCISA Facilities & Property Management
element.documentation: All activities aimed at ensuring that organisational facilities and properties are fit for purpose, future-proofed and maintained to the appropriate standards, including security and health and safety.

element.name: UCISA Graduation Record Certificate Mgt
element.documentation: What the organisation does to ensure accurate records, relating to the formal qualifications awarded to students, are produced and maintained. This includes degree award certificates, Diploma Supplements and other associated certificates and records, and the ability to provide records and certificates as required.

element.name: UCISA Student Mobility
element.documentation: What the organisation does to ensure students can study and enrol at different universities, either as part of their award at the originating organisation or as a permanent transfer to the other organisation, and, vice-versa, the ability to accept students from other universities in the same fashion.

element.name: UCISA Enrolment Status Mgt
element.documentation: What the organisation does to ensure the change of students' official statuses as members of the organisation in response to requests or changes in situation, and in accordance with the relevant regulations. This includes the abilities to interrupt/suspend studies for a period, withdraw from units of study, programmes of study and/or the organisation, and to transfer between units/modules of study.

element.name: UCISA Graduation Event Mgt
element.documentation: What the organisation does to stage the ceremony at which degrees are formally and publicly conferred by the organisation to eligible graduands. This includes the abilities to make the necessary arrangements for the event(s), and the carrying out of the graduation ceremony itself along with other associated events.

element.name: UCISA Copyright Mgt
element.documentation: What the organisation does to secure data under copyright, including identification, assessment, monitoring and intervention in the case of breach, and ensuring appropriate use of data copyrighted by other persons or organisations.

element.name: UCISA Workforce Relations Mgt
element.documentation: What the organisation does to ensure a positive work environment, focus on individual and collective relationships, including unions, resolve workplace issues through intervention when necessary.

element.name: UCISA Commercial Partner Engagement
element.documentation: What the organisation does to initially identify, engage with, contract, administer and maintain commercial partners.

element.name: UCISA Infrastructure Lifecycle Mgt
element.documentation: What the organisation does to create and manage infrastructure in support of organisational requirements.

element.name: UCISA Other Tertiary Institution Relationship Mgt
element.documentation: What the organisation does to identify key peer tertiary institutions, and manage and maintain these relationships.

element.name: UCISA Research Training
element.documentation: All activities aimed at training and developing the organisation's researchers, including both staff and post-graduate research students.

element.name: UCISA Research Production
element.documentation: What the organisation does to produce research. This is the execution of the research project.

element.name: UCISA Commercialise Research Outcomes
element.documentation: What the organisation does to plan and realise the commercial potential of its research outcomes, including contract and intellectual property management.

element.name: UCISA Commercial Sourcing
element.documentation: All activities aimed at ensuring that the organisation can effectively identify and assess commercial opportunities.

element.name: UCISA Internal Audit & Reporting
element.documentation: What the organisation does to manage and undertake the internal audit and compliance program.

element.name: UCISA Government, Public & Stakeholder Relationships
element.documentation: All activities aimed at ensuring a continuous level of engagement is maintained between the organisation and its customers, stakeholders & other interested parties.

element.name: UCISA Information & Communication Technology Mgt
element.documentation: All activities aimed at the efficient and effective development, delivery and management of ICT resources and access to those resources.

element.name: UCISA Commercial Tenancy
element.documentation: What the organisation does to manage external tenants.

element.name: UCISA Remuneration & Entitlements Mgt
element.documentation: What the organisation does to ensure it rewards its staff appropriately in terms of pay, pension and other benefits.

element.name: UCISA Non-Academic Achievement Mgt
element.documentation: What the organisation does to ensure the recognition and recording of achievements made by students at organisation, other than formal academic awards. This includes abilities to produce HEARs (Higher Education Achievement Reports), recognise outstanding extra-curricular activities and voluntary work, and to bestow intuition-specific prizes.

element.name: UCISA Graduation Eligibility Mgt
element.documentation: What the organisation does to ensure that the administrative and financial (debt) affairs of students are in order, and those eligible to graduate are determined. This does not include academic results or exam/review boards.

element.name: UCISA Student Administration
element.documentation: All activities aimed at maintaining accurate records of students and their administrative and academic statuses during their time at organisation, and managing the change of records and statuses.

element.name: UCISA Staff Recruitment
element.documentation: What the organisation does to ensure the best candidates are recruited to vacant posts, including identification of job requirements, attraction and selection of candidates, hiring and induction.

element.name: UCISA Campus Security
element.documentation: What the organisation does to ensure the safety of the onsite community including monitoring and responding to unacceptable or criminal behaviour.

element.name: UCISA Commercial Partner Integration & Transition
element.documentation: What the organisation does to manage assimilation and change in the relationship with commercial partners.

element.name: UCISA Legal Services
element.documentation: All activities aimed at ensuring the availability of effective legal services.

element.name: UCISA Commercial Contract Performance Mgt
element.documentation: What the organisation does to ensure the process of systematically and efficiently managing contract execution and analysis for the purpose of maximising financial and operational performance and minimising risk.

element.name: UCISA Research Dataset Mgt
element.documentation: What the organisation does to store, share, use and re-use datasets produced from research projects, including dataset management planning and curation of datasets beyond the lifetime of individual projects.

element.name: UCISA Accommodation Departure & Turnaround Mgt
element.documentation: What the organisation does to enable an orderly departure of residents at the end of their tenancy and ensure the accommodation is properly prepared for its next resident.
